Template: [[artifactId]]/contentrepo_db_host
Type: string
Default: localhost
Description: The host that provides the Content Repo database

Template: [[artifactId]]/contentrepo_db_password
Type: password
Default:
Description: The password for the user that will access the Content Repo database

Template: [[artifactId]]/contentrepo_port
Type: string
Default: 8004
Description: The HTTP port you would like content repo to be accessible from

Template: [[artifactId]]/crepo_storage_location
Type: string
Default: mogile
Description: Valid values: "mogile","local". Local is used for local development or vagrants and data is saved on the local filestore. Mogile is used for production-like environments and uses mogile to store data.

Template: [[artifactId]]/contentrepo_mogile_trackers
Type: string
Default:
Description: The Mogile trackers used for storing data. Only used for mogile crepo_storage_location
